WEBVTT

00:00.712 --> 00:02.878
- Oh, this is good.
- Oh, this... look at this one.

00:02.879 --> 00:05.269
Oh, it's so timeless.
It's perfect.

00:05.270 --> 00:07.488
Yeah, timeless, meaning you can wait
two or five years to wear it.

00:07.489 --> 00:08.805
Don't be jealous.

00:08.806 --> 00:10.102
Well, well, well.

00:10.103 --> 00:13.160
If it isn't a young Barbra Streisand
and an old Betty White.

00:13.161 --> 00:15.245
Where is Gay Cyclops?

00:15.246 --> 00:16.858
Still trying
to stumble his way in?

00:16.859 --> 00:18.402
We can't come here anymore.

00:18.403 --> 00:21.668
Rachel, I, uh, brought
an engagement gift for you.

00:21.669 --> 00:22.864
Hmm.

00:25.575 --> 00:27.577
Whoa. Oh, whoa, whoa!
Oh, my God!

00:27.578 --> 00:29.259
Oh, no, that is...
that is Photoshopped.

00:29.260 --> 00:31.540
His thing is not that small
or... or brown.

00:31.541 --> 00:33.291
And he could never fit
into those pumps.

00:33.292 --> 00:35.085
Just think, from
now until eternity,

00:35.086 --> 00:37.935
every time someone
Googles Finn Hudson,

00:37.936 --> 00:41.385
they'll be treated to that
and dozens just like it.

00:41.386 --> 00:44.011
That's the beauty of the Internet.
It stays with us forever.

00:44.012 --> 00:45.679
What do you want, Sebastian?

00:45.680 --> 00:48.598
I want a guaranteed Regionals win,
so I want you to drop out.

00:48.599 --> 00:50.809
McKinley gets home-court
advantage this year.

00:50.810 --> 00:53.534
You're going to come
down with Asian bird flu

00:53.535 --> 00:55.397
or whatever Tina
Blowing-Wang just had.

00:55.398 --> 00:57.149
But that is show choir
terrorism.

00:57.150 --> 01:00.110
You give a bad name
to the entire gay community.

01:00.111 --> 01:02.192
And you give the gay community
cutting-edge fashion

01:02.193 --> 01:04.912
that's usually only seen
on Puerto Rican pride floats.

01:04.913 --> 01:06.575
I'm sorry... I didn't hear you.

01:06.576 --> 01:08.702
I was distracted
by your giant horse teeth.

01:08.703 --> 01:10.746
You have 24 hours
to drop out, Rachel,

01:10.747 --> 01:12.886
or I press the
upload button.

01:18.629 --> 01:20.511
That's it. I'm done.
I'm leaving this classroom,

01:20.512 --> 01:22.215
and I'm going to beat
that Sebastian kid's ass!

01:22.216 --> 01:24.148
- Finn, chill.
- No, I'm not going to chill.

01:24.149 --> 01:25.969
- I... I'm done chilling.
- The official show choir rule book

01:25.970 --> 01:28.388
states that "any real
or perceived threat of violence,

01:28.389 --> 01:30.474
"vandalism or humiliation
will be met with a swift

01:30.475 --> 01:32.156
"and unquestioned
disqualification

01:32.157 --> 01:33.690
of the threatening party's team
with extreme prejudice."

01:33.691 --> 01:34.728
It's right here.

01:34.729 --> 01:37.981
Page 72, by-law 15,
section six, article 44.

01:37.982 --> 01:39.896
Guys, I contacted
the headmaster of Dalton.

01:39.897 --> 01:40.984
Like you did when Sebastian

01:40.985 --> 01:43.195
almost blinded me?
What did they do then?

01:43.196 --> 01:44.821
Same thing as they're
going to do now... nothing.

01:44.822 --> 01:46.420
Look, none of this
matters now anyways, okay?

01:46.421 --> 01:48.205
We're not going to let him
beat us like this.

01:48.206 --> 01:50.757
- I'm going to perform at Regionals.
- Even if he's going to post

01:50.758 --> 01:52.704
a photo like this
of me if you do?

01:52.705 --> 01:54.289
Finn, I'm not going to negotiate
with terrorists.

01:54.290 --> 01:55.916
If someone posted a picture

01:55.917 --> 01:59.216
like that of me online,
I'd probably kill myself.

01:59.217 --> 02:00.587
Twice to be sure
I was dead.

02:00.588 --> 02:03.136
Look, you guys are just going to have
to deal with things like this.

02:03.137 --> 02:05.467
The more successful you get,
the more garbage

02:05.468 --> 02:06.718
people are going to
make up about you.

02:06.719 --> 02:08.192
They're going to love
to tear you down.

02:08.193 --> 02:09.471
I can't believe
you would do that to me.

02:09.472 --> 02:11.478
I'm going to be
married to you.

02:11.479 --> 02:13.266
Don't you think I'm going to
suffer the consequences as well?

02:13.267 --> 02:15.685
I mean, I just... I don't care
about stuff like that.

02:15.686 --> 02:17.868
I love you, and we'll...
we'll manage this together.

02:17.869 --> 02:20.273
Okay, the important thing
right now is that we win.

02:20.274 --> 02:21.955
So you wouldn't care
if I Photoshopped a photo

02:21.956 --> 02:23.443
of you like this
and put it on the Internet?

02:23.444 --> 02:25.792
Look, our future depends
on us winning Regionals.

02:25.793 --> 02:28.031
It'll help me
towards my NYADA application.

02:28.032 --> 02:29.213
Hmm.

02:29.214 --> 02:30.367
Hope you get in.

02:30.368 --> 02:31.701
Finn.

02:36.588 --> 02:39.751
- You wanted to see me?
- Q, have a seat.

02:39.752 --> 02:42.087
Prepare yourself.

02:42.088 --> 02:44.678
I'm about to drop a bomb on you.

02:48.566 --> 02:51.602
I, Sue Sylvester...

02:51.603 --> 02:53.770
am with child.

02:55.141 --> 02:56.143
Are you serious?

02:59.810 --> 03:01.147
Wow.

03:01.148 --> 03:04.693
Um, that's amazing
and confusing.

03:06.360 --> 03:08.446
- Who's the father?
- Oh, I can't tell you that yet.

03:08.447 --> 03:11.588
But here's the deal.
In order for this zygote

03:11.589 --> 03:13.674
to stay firmly ensconced
in my uterine wall,

03:13.675 --> 03:15.745
my doctor has put me
on bovine hormones

03:15.746 --> 03:18.164
that are making me
extremely nauseous.

03:18.165 --> 03:20.709
They've also given me a
near-superhuman sense of smell.

03:20.710 --> 03:22.266
For instance,
I can tell

03:22.267 --> 03:23.767
that within the last week,
you either enjoyed

03:23.768 --> 03:25.636
a delicious curry
or a hug from Principal Figgins.

03:25.637 --> 03:29.222
Well, you know,
morning sickness is a good sign.

03:29.223 --> 03:31.720
It means that the baby
is developing properly.

03:31.721 --> 03:34.097
Well, it's good for the baby,
not so good for me.

03:34.098 --> 03:37.809
Well, you know, there really
is no cure for morning sickness.

03:37.810 --> 03:40.400
I mean, I ate saltines,

03:40.401 --> 03:43.440
drank herbal tea
and sucked on lollipops.

03:43.441 --> 03:44.955
That helps.

03:44.956 --> 03:46.943
Lollipops?
Yeah.

03:46.944 --> 03:50.460
Weird, but it works.

03:50.461 --> 03:52.162
Well, thank you, Q,

03:52.163 --> 03:54.464
for that condescending tone
and barely helpful advice.

03:58.136 --> 04:00.921
I wanted to ask you a favor,
actually, Coach.

04:02.291 --> 04:03.668
I would love
to rejoin the Cheerios!

04:03.669 --> 04:05.676
I beg your pardon?
It's my senior year,

04:05.677 --> 04:07.210
and I want to finish high school

04:07.211 --> 04:08.673
in a Cheerios! uniform
with a national championship.

04:08.674 --> 04:10.759
I mean,
other than Glee,

04:10.760 --> 04:12.886
this was the rest
of my high school experience.

04:12.887 --> 04:16.403
Well, I'm sorry, Q,
but that wouldn't be fair

04:16.404 --> 04:19.434
to the girls who've been practicing
all year long, who didn't quit.

04:19.435 --> 04:22.909
And if you'll now please
get the hell out of my office.

04:22.910 --> 04:24.661
I just caught a whiff
of hot dog water

04:24.662 --> 04:26.563
wafting in from the cafeteria,

04:26.564 --> 04:29.194
and I think I'm going to blow
some serious chunks.

04:29.195 --> 04:31.118
Excuse me.

04:38.009 --> 04:40.877
You okay?
You seemed upset.

04:42.123 --> 04:44.584
- And if Sebastian thinks...
- Forget about Sebastian!

04:44.585 --> 04:46.717
I'm not mad at
you. I just...

04:46.718 --> 04:48.802
don't want to waste
any more time on him.

04:48.803 --> 04:51.254
I-I want to focus on winning.

04:52.591 --> 04:54.424
I've got a new song
I want to try out.

04:54.425 --> 04:55.776
