08:03.949 --> 08:06.494
We have to be
very careful about how

08:06.495 --> 08:08.496
we deliver the news of this
to the student body.

08:08.497 --> 08:10.066
David was part
of this community,

08:10.067 --> 08:12.208
and he still has
many friends here.

08:12.209 --> 08:15.795
And my understanding
is that these teen suicides...

08:15.796 --> 08:20.175
or even attempts like David's...
can induce a string of copycats.

08:20.176 --> 08:21.342
It's just so senseless.

08:21.343 --> 08:23.303
Facebook,
Twitter, Tumblr.

08:23.304 --> 08:25.096
The pressure to protect
your reputation

08:25.097 --> 08:26.639
is so much worse
than when we were kids.

08:26.640 --> 08:29.267
Yeah, and these people
can sling their hatred

08:29.268 --> 08:30.477
and their mud
anonymously.

08:32.186 --> 08:33.640
Sue, are you crying?

08:34.859 --> 08:37.734
- Hormones.
- No, it's not hormones.

08:38.986 --> 08:40.764
I could have done more.

08:40.765 --> 08:43.198
I was principal when Dave
was having his trouble

08:43.198 --> 08:44.949
with Porcelain, and...

08:44.950 --> 08:47.404
I knew there was something
up with that kid. I knew it.

08:49.703 --> 08:51.748
All I can think of
is his dad finding him.

08:51.749 --> 08:54.494
Get some help! David, no!
Buddy, come on.

08:54.495 --> 08:55.919
David!

08:57.332 --> 08:59.339
And that feeling.

08:59.340 --> 09:01.301
Guys, we were all hard on Dave.

09:01.302 --> 09:03.551
We thought he
was going to hurt Kurt.

09:03.552 --> 09:06.971
I just never thought
he'd hurt himself.

09:06.972 --> 09:10.266
- It wasn't our job to know.
- Then whose job was it?

09:13.812 --> 09:15.315
We should start today's meeting

09:15.316 --> 09:17.565
by praying for Karofsky.

09:17.566 --> 09:20.485
That he finds peace and
that he feels better.

09:20.486 --> 09:22.028
I think we should
start today's meeting

09:22.029 --> 09:23.279
by praying for his family.

09:23.280 --> 09:25.615
They could use comfort
more than he could.

09:25.616 --> 09:26.950
I just don't understand how

09:26.951 --> 09:29.160
he could get to such
a horrible, dark place.

09:29.161 --> 09:30.411
It's all over Facebook.

09:30.412 --> 09:33.867
A couple of kids from
Karofsky's new school

09:33.868 --> 09:36.626
saw him at Breadstix with
Kurt on Valentine's Day.

09:36.627 --> 09:38.503
They posted mean
stuff on his page

09:38.504 --> 09:40.290
and texted everyone
that he was gay.

09:41.492 --> 09:44.259
- He couldn't take it.
- How is he?

09:44.260 --> 09:46.496
- Is he going to live?
- Well, he's in the hospital,

09:46.497 --> 09:48.471
but thank God his dad
found him in time.

09:48.472 --> 09:50.932
I feel sorry for Karofsky,

09:50.933 --> 09:53.393
but what he did
was selfish.

09:53.394 --> 09:55.395
He didn't just want to hurt
himself; he wanted to hurt

09:55.396 --> 09:56.604
everyone around him.

09:56.605 --> 09:59.009
I went through the wringer,
but I never

09:59.010 --> 10:00.566
- got to that place.
- Quinn, please.

10:00.567 --> 10:03.447
Sure, you had a baby
when you were 16

10:03.448 --> 10:06.072
and you had a bad dye job
for two weeks,

10:06.073 --> 10:08.950
but seriously? The world never
stopped loving you.

10:08.951 --> 10:10.994
And you're
going to Yale.

10:10.995 --> 10:13.037
You have no idea what Karofsky
was struggling with.

10:13.038 --> 10:15.039
You really want to try
to compare...

10:15.040 --> 10:17.500
The despair, the
self-loathing.

10:17.501 --> 10:18.918
It doesn't matter.

10:18.919 --> 10:21.548
I just can't imagine things
getting so messed-up

10:21.549 --> 10:23.631
that you would consider
taking your own life.

10:23.632 --> 10:26.136
That is so harsh and reductive.

10:26.137 --> 10:27.552
Have some compassion.

10:27.553 --> 10:30.179
Do you know what they're still
writing on his Facebook?

10:30.180 --> 10:32.765
"Better luck next time"
and "Try, try again."

10:32.766 --> 10:33.933
Why are you even
here, Kurt?

10:33.934 --> 10:35.762
Thought you didn't
believe in God.

10:37.682 --> 10:40.231
He asked me if he could come,
and I invited him.

10:40.232 --> 10:45.155
I heard you guys were praying
for Karofsky, and...

10:45.156 --> 10:47.223
after everything
that we've been through,

10:47.224 --> 10:49.392
I didn't have
anywhere else to go.

10:55.579 --> 10:57.868
I feel responsible.

10:59.921 --> 11:03.757
He asked me out, and...

11:03.758 --> 11:05.048
I said no.

11:08.050 --> 11:09.052
And he kept calling me...

11:12.262 --> 11:14.807
<i>If I'd just answered one
of those stupid calls...</i>

11:18.589 --> 11:21.147
We're taking a edible
arrangement to the hospital.

11:22.940 --> 11:24.528
Do you want to come with us?

11:31.819 --> 11:32.825
I'm so sorry.

11:32.826 --> 11:34.938
I'm sorry.
I'm really sorry.

11:38.042 --> 11:40.124
Look, I've been thinking
about what Dave did,

11:40.125 --> 11:41.918
and I just want you to know
that there's nothing

11:41.919 --> 11:45.499
that anybody could do and there's
nothing that anybody could say about me

11:45.500 --> 11:47.173
that would make me
want to do that.

11:47.174 --> 11:49.753
Good, 'cause I don't ever want
to be without you.

11:51.593 --> 11:54.931
So, I'm not gonna
perform at Regionals.

11:54.932 --> 11:57.511
You have to. Look, I don't care
about these pictures.

11:57.512 --> 11:59.312
I don't care about what anybody
says about me...

11:59.313 --> 12:00.463
except for you.

12:08.193 --> 12:09.987
Life's too short.

12:09.988 --> 12:11.906
- What?
- Look, I don't want to wait

12:11.907 --> 12:14.411
for some arbitrary date
to start living it, I...

12:14.412 --> 12:16.863
I want to get married.

12:16.864 --> 12:18.121
Now.

12:18.122 --> 12:19.622
I have gym.
No, it's Saturday.

12:19.623 --> 12:22.041
After we win Regionals.

12:22.042 --> 12:23.584
Seriously?

12:23.585 --> 12:25.294
Yeah.
Awesome!

12:27.324 --> 12:28.756
But wait, what...

12:28.757 --> 12:30.127
what if we lose?

12:30.128 --> 12:32.295
Well, I thought we agreed
that I was singing.

12:40.638 --> 12:44.605
Let me break it down for you,
from one bitch to another.

12:44.606 --> 12:46.107
All this vicious,
underhanded crap

12:46.108 --> 12:47.900
has got to stop.
Exactly.

12:47.901 --> 12:49.110
That's why
I called you here.

12:49.111 --> 12:50.697
First of all...

12:50.698 --> 12:52.649
Blaine,
I am sorry about your eye.

12:52.650 --> 12:53.656
That means
nothing to me.

12:53.657 --> 12:55.908
Just give me a chance.
I have no excuses,

12:55.909 --> 13:00.371
other than a lame prank got
completely out of control.

13:00.372 --> 13:02.790
Second, the Finn photos have
all been destroyed.

13:02.791 --> 13:05.084
I want the Warblers
to win fair and square.

13:05.085 --> 13:07.030
And we're gonna take donations

13:07.031 --> 13:08.504
for Lady Gaga's Born This Way
Foundation.

13:08.505 --> 13:10.083
Win, lose or draw,

13:10.084 --> 13:13.092
we're gonna dedicate our
performance to Dave Karofsky.

13:13.093 --> 13:15.678
I thought you might
want to join us.

13:15.679 --> 13:17.847
Wait for the punch,
you know it's coming.

13:17.848 --> 13:19.926
No, not this time.

13:19.927 --> 13:25.855
For too long I have treated
everything like a big joke.

13:25.856 --> 13:28.735
So, how do you get
a guy to like you?

13:28.736 --> 13:31.404
You, get a guy? Please.

13:31.405 --> 13:34.057
Why, what's wrong with me?

13:34.058 --> 13:36.824
First off, you're about
100 pounds overweight.

13:37.361 --> 13:40.244
Quit waxing your eyebrows.
You look like Liberace.

13:40.245 --> 13:43.915
In fact, just stay in
the closet, buddy.

13:46.037 --> 13:48.255
It's all fun and games...

13:48.256 --> 13:49.295
until it's not.

13:52.176 --> 13:55.468
Mr. Shue, why do you have a jar
of peanut butter with one spoon?

13:55.469 --> 13:56.886
Yeah, there are 15 of us here,

13:56.887 --> 13:58.748
and I'm only comfortable

13:58.749 --> 14:01.098
sharing a spoon
with about half of you.

14:01.099 --> 14:02.519
Well, it's come to my attention

14:02.520 --> 14:04.685
that our good friend Rory Flanagan
has never tasted peanut butter.

14:04.686 --> 14:06.979
- What?!
- Are you serious?

14:06.980 --> 14:08.189
- No way.
- It's not possible.

14:08.190 --> 14:09.926
Rory, if you don't mind.

14:13.114 --> 14:14.597
Oh, God...

14:18.031 --> 14:20.070
Oh, my God...

14:20.071 --> 14:21.452
That's the best thing
I've ever had.

14:22.704 --> 14:28.584
Mr. Shuester, wow, that's
incredibly moving,

14:28.585 --> 14:30.294
Yeah, Mr. Shue,
what's the point of all this?

14:30.295 --> 14:32.004
The point is

14:32.005 --> 14:33.416
Rory just had
a brand-new experience,

14:33.417 --> 14:35.091
something as simple
as peanut butter.

14:35.092 --> 14:36.259
You guys are young.

14:37.050 --> 14:39.172
I want you to promise me

